{
  "stem": "2966.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was wonderful to see them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was my uncle, aunt, and two children, a boy and a girl.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My aunt was my mother system.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her name was Dora.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my uncle was Bernard.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Later they emigrated to Israel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "While I was doing research, trying through the Red Cross, International Red Cross, and through other organizations, I found out that my sister was taken together with 2,000 women-- Jewish women-- on a ship on the Baltic sea, and sunk, purposely.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was our very civilized and cultured Germany, which I have to argue with everybody till today because some people have very short memories.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Where my father died, I don't know, could never find out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it had to be between January 1 of '45 and the end of the war, which was only four months.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After the three day pass, I came back to the ship, and I kept sailing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was sailing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then in 1949, I signed up as a crew member on the first Israeli ship that Israeli-- Israel bought here.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the crew here, with the Israeli captain, took the ship to Israel.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In Israel, I was about two weeks, and there I met my family that just arrived from Israel-- from Germany from the DP camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I looked at them up, and they lived in a very poor conditions there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was right after the '48 war-- the war of survival.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the conditions were very rough there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They lived like in tents.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had no place to cook there, no place to wash or anything.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But because my cousin got married in the DP camp in Germany, which is also a little story, and her husband was a famous soccer player, which was very sought for in Israel.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
